11 An Act relating to schools; amending Section 1,
Chapter 106, O.S.L. 2022 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
12 11-201), which relates to the library media program;
prohibiting community standards from including
13 sexually explicit conduct; defining term; and
providing an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 1, Chapter 106, O.S.L.
18 2022 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 11-201), is amended to read as
19 follows:
20 Section 11-201. As school library media center resources are
21 finite, the library media program shall be reflective of the
22 community standards for the population the library media center
23 serves when acquiring an age-appropriate collection of print
24 materials, nonprint materials, multimedia resources, equipment, and
HB2978 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 supp lies adequate in quality and quantity to meet the needs of
2 students in all areas of the school library media program. For
3 purposes of this section, "community standards" shall not include
4 depictions nor descriptions of sexually explicit conduct as defined
5 in Section 1024.1 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
6 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
7
